title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1987-03-30

description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street, It's All Over Now, Stagger Lee, Good Time Blues, Box Of Rain, Loser, Cassidy

Set 2

Iko Iko, Saint Of Circumstance-> He's Gone-> Jam-> Drums-> Space-> Truckin'-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text:
I'm the first? I can't believe no one else has reviewed this show yet!
I never comment on any of the shows but I need to break my silence for this one...
This has to be one of the best recordings of any show!  The guitars are so clean! The symbols? Oh My God.  The symbols are like waves pushing the music forward. Jerry's voice is spot on...
It's All Over Now, Baby Blue has got to be one of the best versions out there.  The rhythm is perfect...
The Loser? Cassidy?  It's All Over Now?  Fabulous...
Phil Zone When Phil comes out this spicy right from the get go, you know it’s gonna be a good one. Don’t say I didn’t warn ya.
